main event: A civilian observed a bright, silver, round object traveling in a straight line at a very high altitude in Chicago, Illinois on March 31, 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared to be much higher than two aircraft that flew by at the time.
The object was described as looking like a star, but was traveling rapidly in a straight line.
No sound or tail/trail was observed.
The sighting was considered a possible satellite by the air force.
